  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "(Fresh Graduates) Information Technology Services Procurement Officer (Banking IT Professional Services)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>What we are looking for (Domain: Software Application Vendor):</strong></u></p>\n<p>- Experienced hire whom is focused on IT Services Sourcing &amp; Procurement, understand the IT services nuances to facilitate on the negotiation with suppliers.</p>\n<p>- Join the Strategic Sourcing Team to review and negotiate IT contracts with suppliers on IT initiatives across the Bank.</p>\n<p>- Familiar with IT contractual clauses to negotiate with suppliers, as one of the key deliverables of the scope is to review contracts for this role. Good knowledge on information technology contractual clauses:</p>\n<p>* Scope of IT Services</p>\n<p>* Payment Milestones</p>\n<p>* Min Wage</p>\n<p>* Man Days Estimation</p>\n<p>* Confidentiality Agreement</p>\n<p>* Intellectual Property/Ownership</p>\n<p>* Breaches &amp; Indemnity</p>\n<p>* Governing Law &amp; Jusrisdication</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Department:</strong></u></p>\n<p>Professional Services are a group of external workers whom the client Bank has a contractual agreement with their companies to provide services (and/or workers) for the client bank. Examples of contracted services will include consulting projects (i.e. fixed fee / time and material) and outsourced services.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Job Description:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Review and negotiate IT contracts with suppliers on IT initiatives across the Bank.</li>\n  <li>Working in close collaboration with the IT Sourcing &amp; Procurement Department colleagues, Group Legal and IT stakeholders to protect the Bank and to optimize the value from the supply market.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance to Client Bank's policies, process standards and guidelines.</li>\n  <li>Provide advice on contracts, explain impact of contract gaps and mitigate contract risks to the stakeholders effectively and collaboratively.</li>\n  <li>Ensure the right risk culture through strong communication lines with stakeholders and colleagues.</li>\n</ul>",
